element.text:
Stand up, Arnis Warrior.
Your journey doesn't end here.

Congratulations!
You defeated the monsters and saved the world!
Thanks for playing!

Did you know?
Arnis was formerly known as the pre-Hispanic Filipino word,
kali, or eskrima which is Spanish for fencing.

Did you know?
Arnis was banned during the Spanish colonization period
as it was seen as deadly form of self-defense.

Did you know?
Arnis was developed to fit a person's natural movement
rather than adjusting to the martial art.

Did you know?
Arnis is a combat sport focusing on 
weapon disarming and defending oneself from attacks.

A & D - To Move
SPACE - To Jump
J - To Attack
